  "text": "With developments in phylogenetic analyses, and an increasing ability to coordinate research efforts around the world, large-scale comparisons of cognition across multiple species are set to revolutionize the way we investigate the evolution of intelligence [CITATION_1] . However, this type of work is only as robust as the comparative tests used. If factors other than variation in cognition can systematically affect the performance of a subset of the animals tested, there is a real danger that faulty conclusions will be drawn.",
